# Firebase Configuration
# Get these values from your Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 1. Create a new project or select existing one
# 2. Go to Project Settings > Your apps > Web app
# 3. Copy the configuration values below

NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-auth-domain.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to .env.local (without .example)
# 2. Replace all "your-*-here" values with your actual Firebase credentials
# 3. Enable Authentication > Google provider in Firebase Console
# 4. Enable Firestore Database in Firebase Console
# 5. Set Firestore rules to allow authenticated users to read/write their own data

